title: College GameDay at Michigan on Saturday
text:
ESPN's College GameDay broadcasting from Ann Arbor for Michigan State versus Michigan 11:47 PM, Oct 10, 2015 11:47 PM, Oct 10, 2015 Show Caption Previous Next 
ANN ARBOR, Mich. (WYXZ) - ESPN announced late Saturday night that its College GameDay show will be broadcasting from Ann Arbor on Saturday, Oct. 17 for the Michigan State versus Michigan game. 
With the Wolverines' win over Northwestern and the Spartans' win over Rutgers, the game could be the most important between the two in nearly a decade. 
Earlier this year, GameDay was in East Lansing when the Oregon Ducks took on the Spartans. 
The show airs from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. Saturdays on ESPN. We're coming, @umichfootball ! See you in a week. pic.twitter.com/w0UFTVLpFI
